# Trivy ignore file — container vulnerability suppressions.
# RULE: every entry MUST carry a justification + a revisit condition.
# Format:
#   CVE-XXXX-YYYY  # <why not exploitable in our runtime> — revisit when <condition>

# Kubernetes misconfig: "image from an untrusted registry". We intentionally run pinned official
# third-party images from Docker Hub — protomaps/go-pmtiles (basemap tile server) and svhd/logto
# (auth) — which have no first-party DO-registry equivalent. They are pinned by version tag.
# Revisit when: we mirror these into our DigitalOcean registry (then drop this + use ${REGISTRY}).
AVD-KSV-0125

# uuid@7.0.3 out-of-bounds write — reached ONLY via the Expo build toolchain
# (expo → @expo/config-plugins → xcode@3.0.1), a BUILD-TIME prebuild dependency that
# parses Xcode project files; it is not bundled into the shipped iOS/Android app, so the
# flaw is not reachable at app runtime. The fixed line (uuid 11+) is a breaking major bump
# that xcode@3.0.1 cannot consume, so we cannot force it without breaking `expo prebuild`.
# Pre-existing on main; gating scanners (pnpm-audit high/critical, trivy-fs secrets) pass.
# Revisit when: @expo/config-plugins / xcode upgrade their uuid dependency to a fixed line.
CVE-2026-41907

# postcss@8.4.31 XSS via improper escaping — a BUILD-TIME web tooling dependency (Next.js /
# Tailwind compile pipeline); PostCSS does not process untrusted stylesheet input at app
# runtime, so the flaw is not reachable in the deployed app. Pre-existing on main.
# Revisit when: the web build toolchain bumps postcss to >= 8.5.10.
CVE-2026-41305
